  "text": "• Uremia: Polyneuropathy is one of the most frequent manifestations in chronic uremia. Hemodialyzed uremic patients have been found to have vitamin B 6 deficiency which may lead to paresthesia [CITATION_1] . Uremia can also cause restless legs syndrome which is clinically defined as an urge to move the legs with or without associated paresthesia [CITATION_2] .",
